                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Winterle/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-02T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 2, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 2—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Embassy’s 21, October 2, 3 p.m. Following from American Consul at Chefoo:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“October 2, 8 a.m. From October 1, 8 p.m. no bus due to the rain. Am
                            going by automobile at noon if roads dry, otherwise tomorrow. Following
                            has just arrived from the Japanese Consulate: <pb facs="1207" n="1095"
                                xml:id="pg_1095"/>
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>[‘] I have the honor to refer to the case of difficulties between
                                    Japanese and Americans which occurred early last month and to
                                    inform you the case will be easily settled if your Embassy will
                                    authorize you to recognize the participation of American Navy
                                    enlisted personnel and to express either orally or in writing
                                    your regret for this occurrence.[’]”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
